CHIJIOKE AMUNNADI is a Nigerian poet. He is the winner of the inaugural 2002 ANA Gabriel Okara Prize for Poetry with pilgrim’s passage, as well as the inaugural Glenna Luschei Prize. He is the author of fire within, a river’s journey, and a field of echoes. To write a poem You break the shell and pour your white and yolk into a bowl add pepper, spices salt of metaphors beat mind and lines into one whole poem and pour into a page or your twitter pan beneath it, gas-lighting all kinds of fire, fury and usual flame eyes until everything cooks name, poem and sense ready to be devoured. 